{"ID":7662019,"Work Item Type":"Bug","Title":"Security bug : Test app can generate an SSO token for any other app","Description":"<div><b>Repro steps:</b> </div><div><ol><li>Copy the &quot;webApplicationInfo&quot; of any app to your test app </li><li>Try to invoke the &quot;silentAuth&quot; flow in your test app </li><li>Both Outlook web and desktop will generate the token and send it to your app </li> </ol><div><b>Impact:</b> </div> </div><div>The test app can do anything with the generated token on-behalf-of the user against any app's resource </div><div><br> </div><div><b>Teams:</b><br>Teams validates if the &quot;webApplicationInfo.resource&quot; uri contains the caller app's BotId or not (<a href=\"https://domoreexp.visualstudio.com/Teamspace/_git/teams-modular-packages?path=/packages/services/io/services-io-bots-platform/src/bots-platform-service.ts&amp;_a=contents&amp;version=GBmaster\">reference</a>). {"ID":7725835,"Work Item Type":"Bug","Title":"MERenderer Integ(OWA) - Conversation specific data storage issue when both main window and pop-up window mails opened","Description":"<div>Useful context: </div><div><ul><li style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">Currently we maintain a global object containing conversation specific data like conversationId, mailbox info, copycard &amp; delete callback useful for handling me-renderer card events in OWA. </li><li style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">This object gets overridden whenever we render a new card with that corresponding data. </li> </ul> </div><div>Root cause: </div><div><ul><li>Issue occurs when we open a new compose window in pop up mode and a consume mail in main window. Now the object will have data corresponding to mail for which last card rendered.&nbsp; </li><li>Now if insert a new card in pop up mail, object will be updated with pop up mail data. And then if we try to copy card from button of any main window's card it fails because handler in the global object is corresponding to the pop-up mail. </li> </ul><div>Possible fix: </div> </div><div><ul><li>We can maintain card specific data in map with key as cardId instead of a single conversation specific data getting updated every time a new card is inserted. </li><li>Need more thinking on this if there is a better solution. </li> </ul> </div><div><br> </div><div><br> </div><div><br> </div><div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;display:inline !important;\">Note</span><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;display:inline !important;\">:&nbsp;</span> </div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><ul style=\"box-sizing:border-box;padding:0px 0px 0px 40px;\"><li style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;display:inline !important;\">Enable<span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">&nbsp;</span></span><i style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">me-renderer-enabled</i><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;display:inline !important;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">&nbsp;</span>flag</span> </li><li style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;display:inline !important;\">Disable&nbsp;<i style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">me-action-command-enabled</i><span>&nbsp;</span>and&nbsp;<span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><span dir=ltr style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><i style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">me-task-module</i></span></span></span> </li> </ul> </div><br> </div>","Priority":2,"State":"Resolved","Tags":"MERenderer-OWA; MERenderer-OWA-Bugs; OutlookME; OWA; Triaged","Area Path":"OC\\ME\\Outlook\\OWA","Created Date":"3/23/2023 2:59:19 PM","Assigned To":"Dyanesh Kodidasu <dkodidasu@microsoft.com>","Activated By":"","Activated Date":"","Resolved By":"Ashish Singh <ashishsi@microsoft.com>","Resolved Date":"5/5/2023 1:44:53 PM"}
